            <p>To determine the ideal specifications for your exernal HDD, please refer to the
                following formula:<equation-inline>[Output log numbers for a single agent per day] x
                    [Log storage period in days] x [Total number of agents]</equation-inline></p>
            <p>Example: External HDD size for 20,000 agents</p>
            <ul id="ul_tmr_d3z_c5b">
                <li>
                    <p>Output log numbers for a single agent per day: 100 events</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Log storage period in days: 30 days</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>Total number of agents: 20,000 agents</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>Total number of logs: <equation-block id="equation-block_om5_j3z_c5b">100 x 30 x
                    20000 = 60,000,000 Logs</equation-block></p>
            <p>In this case, it would be required to prepare 100 GB for storage space.</p>
